According to the established model for nucleation and growth of thin films52,53, the perovskite formation process can be divided into four steps: (i) formation of a crystal nucleus, (ii) evolution of nuclei into an island structure, (iii) formation of a networked microstructure, and (iv) growth of networks into a continuous film. The Gibbs free energy for heterogeneous nucleation in the first step can be expressed as Eq. (1)1△Gheterogeneous=△Ghomogeneous×fθ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
